msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Italian illustrated herbal, with a group of texts in English, Latin, and Spanish about Morocco added less than a century later.
msContents.textLang: Plant names in Latin, with a few words in Italian (f. 2r-53v); texts about Morocco in English, Spanish, and Latin (54r-97v); glossary of words in Arabic, Spanish, and Latin (f. 98r-101r)

msItem.title: Notes on the plants of Morocco and their uses, f. 54r
Names of cities, towns and mountains in the provinces of Fez, Tremecen, and Tunis, f. 72r
The regid of Morocus [Spanish with English title], f. 82r
The citty of Morocus, Customes of the citty of Morocus, f. 89r
Customes, estates, and offices of the court of Mulley Hamed , f. 90v
Index to the notes on the plants of Morocco, f. 97v
Nomina substantiva [glossary in Latin, Spanish, and Arabic, f. 98r

collation.p: Paper, ii + 102 + ii; 1¹ 2²⁸ 3²⁴ 4⁴⁴ 5⁸; [1-53], 1-17 [=54-70], [71-102]; contemporary foliation in ink, upper right recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in italic script, by at least two hands (f. 2-53, and f. 1, 54-101).

decoDesc.decoNote: 110 colored wash drawings of plants with roots and flowers (f. 2-53).

binding.p: Parchment contemporary with later texts, gilt, with stamp of eagle and child on covers; remnants of 2 pairs of green silk ties; title (Herbal) written on spine in ink.

origin.p: Herbal illustrated in Italy, ca. 1520 (f. 2r-53v); texts on Morocco written in England, ca. 1600 (f. 1r-v, 54r-101r).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by the Latham family of Lancashire (crest of eagle and child on covers) and by Thomas and Edward Syddell (16th-century inscription, f. 1r).
Sold at auction at Bonhams, Dec. 1995.
Sold by Sam Fogg Ltd. (London) to Lawrence J. Schoenberg, June 1996.
Gift of Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle in honor of Lynn Ransom, Project Manager, Schoenberg Database of Manuscripts, 2012.
